lign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> SoL in CGW</span><hr size=1> Just received my newest edition of Computer Gaming World, and what do I see? Fironia Vie riding a horse on the cover! Here's some of the choicer cuts from the review:<br>
<br>
&quot;A moon where the good and evil cat-people keep on fighting their old war; where vampyres prey on all races, where vacuum worms, fungal fiends, and rockhoppers lurk.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;They're shooting for about 24 new zones, though they may exceed that number. The zones will be large, but not quite as large as the Dreadlands in Kunark (to give you longtime players a reference point.)&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, look at those huge spires sprinkled throughout Norrath; those are the transports. You'll need an item in your possession-yet to be determined, but [Associate Producer Gordon] Wrinn assures us it would be easy for all<br>
players to get.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;The bad news is that-as with the current game's boats- you'll still have to wait. The teleport activates periodically, so you will need to be there ahead of time.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Sony Online is still fiddling with the abilities that the Vah Shir will get, but it looks like you can expect them to have infravision, Sneak, and Safe-Fall as native abilities.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;When you dismount, the horse will be unsummoned.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;If you do choose to fight on horseback, you can do so only while the horse is not running. There will be no Apache-style bow fights while riding.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Appropriate classes like Paladins and Shadow Knights may get a Summon Warhorse spell.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;We'll have items that give faction boost while wearing them and other things like a fire sword that's useful against an ice-based creature, but not a fire monster, for example.&quot;<br>
<br>
There's a lot more, like blurbs on the new wizzie familiars, but you'll have to either:<br>
<br>
A: buy the mag yourself.<br>
<br>
B: bribe me with Dr Pepper and BBQ Pringles. Lots of them. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Gortha Strongwill<br>
Dorf of the 29th Bloodforge<br>
